annibals and other deviant diners, and Kantian nausea, Taste resituates Romanticism as a period that naturally saw the rise of the restaurant and the pleasures of the table as a cultural field for the practice of aesthetics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAesthetics, British. 0aAliments dans la littérature. 0aEnglish literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aEsthétique britannique. 0aFood habits in literature. 0aFood in literature. 0aGastronomie dans la littérature. 0aGastronomy in literature. 0aGôut dans le littérature. 0aHabitudes alimentaires dans la littérature. 0aLittérature anglaisexHistoire et critique. 0aTaste in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300133059423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300133059.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles